The Windows restricted-token sandbox implementation under `src/` is a vendored
and modified subset of `codex-rs/windows-sandbox-rs` from openai/codex. It has
been reduced to the non-elevated (restricted-token) capture path and decoupled
from the `codex_protocol`, `codex_otel`, and `codex_utils_*` crates.

Vendored from openai/codex at commit
be338ee9a28ce5a1c75455343e9712aded82c70f. See SYNCING.md for how upstream
changes are tracked and re-applied.

Modifications from upstream:
  * Removed the elevated backend, WFP network filtering, sandbox-account
    provisioning, ConPTY/unified-exec sessions, deny-read ACLs, DPAPI, and OTEL.
  * Replaced `ResolvedWindowsSandboxPermissions`'s `codex_protocol` construction
    with a self-contained one (cwd-aware workspace roots + extra writable roots
    + temp; always deny .git/.codex/.agents inside writable roots).
  * Inlined `codex_utils_string::take_bytes_at_char_boundary`.
  * Added to the capture path: a kill-on-close job object containing the
    sandboxed process tree, and optional live streaming of child stdout/stderr
    (`stream_output` flag).

